Easiest way to handle multiple values is via an `includes` check against an array of values.

```var qualifiedValues = ['Value A', 'Value B'];

if (qualifiedValues.includes(value)) { 
  // Value is qualified 
} else {
  // Value is unqualified
} ```
You could reverse the logic too and create a disqualified list and check that - all depends on how many values are qualified/unqualified.
